1.	Histogram for all variables in a dataset mtcars. Write a program to create histograms for all columns.
Solution:
> library(purrr)
> library(tidyr)
> library(ggplot2)
> 
> 
> mtcars %>%
+     keep(is.numeric) %>%
+     gather() %>%
+     ggplot(aes(value)) +
+     facet_wrap(~ key,scales = "free") +
+     geom_histogram()
